content.description: Starts on the left side of the tower, traverses right to good ledges, then straight up pulling onto the big ledge, then a couple of face moves to the top.
content.protection: TR, there is a rusty piton you can use as a directional.
content.location: Goes left to right and then straight up to the big ledge.

content.description: HARD crux on the top half, crimp move to layback on smears to the top. Bottom half is a jog haul.
content.protection: TR, rusty pin for a directional at the bottom.
content.location: Two variations both starting on the left of the front side of the tower. Either do the first half of Schu Horn and then traverse left in to the crux or go straight up the left arete. The Schu Horn start has more value.

content.description: Most overhanging piece of rock (that isn't a Boulder Problem) in the park. Mainly dry in the rain. A few routes are on it with a few variations of these routes
